.TH MOCKOTO 1 "__DATE__" "mockoto __VERSION__" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mockoto \- generate C mocks and language bindings from C headers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mockoto
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIheader.h\fR [\fIheader2.h\fR ...] [\fB--\fR \fIclang-options\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mockoto
parses one or more C header files and generates output according to the selected mode.

Input headers are compiled by libclang, so include paths and preprocessor definitions
should be passed after
.B -- .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --mode " c|h|rkt|chibi|chicken"
Select output mode.

\fBc\fR (default): generate mock implementation C code.

\fBh\fR: generate mock header declarations.

\fBrkt\fR: generate Racket bindings.

\fBchibi\fR: generate Chibi Scheme FFI stubs.

\fBchicken\fR: generate CHICKEN Scheme bindings using crunch forms.
.TP
.B --print-src
Print source path comments in generated output.
.TP
.B --include-static
Include static functions in generated output.
.TP
.BI --path-exclude " pattern"
Exclude declarations from files whose path contains
.IR pattern .
Can be provided multiple times.
.TP
.BI --path-include " include-path"
Add an include path hint to generated bindings.
Can be provided multiple times.
.TP
.B -V
Show mockoto version and exit.
.TP
.B --version
Show LLVM/clang command line version information.
.TP
.B --help
Show command help from LLVM command line parser.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate mock C implementation:
.IP
.EX
mockoto --mode c server.h -- -I.
.EE
.TP
Generate mock header:
.IP
.EX
mockoto --mode h server.h -- -I.
.EE
.TP
Generate Racket bindings:
.IP
.EX
mockoto --mode rkt client.h server.h -- -I.
.EE
.TP
Generate Chibi stub:
.IP
.EX
mockoto --mode chibi client.h server.h -- -I.
.EE
.TP
Generate CHICKEN bindings:
.IP
.EX
mockoto --mode chicken client.h server.h -- -I.
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B non-zero
Failure while parsing arguments, running clang tooling, or generating output.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR clang (1),
.BR cmake (1)
